# Supabase Query Patterns

## Estrutura

- One query per file; function name in camelCase (ex.: `get-patients-by-user-phone.ts` → `getPatientsByUserPhone`).
- Supabase client **always first argument**: `(supabase: SupabaseClient, ...args)`.
- Never instantiate the client inside the query; caller injects it.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
export async function getPatientById(supabase: SupabaseClient, id: string): Promise<Patient | null> {
  const { data, error } = await supabase
    .from('patients')
    .select('id, name, birth_date, contact_phone, user_phone')
    .eq('id', id)
    .maybeSingle();
  if (error) throw new Error(`Failed to get patient: ${error.message}`);
  return data;
}
```

## Select Explícito

Use explicit column list; avoid `select('*')` unless all columns are needed.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
.select('id, name, birth_date, contact_phone, user_phone')

// ❌ AVOID (unless all cols truly needed)
.select('*')
```

## Single vs MaybeSingle

| Situação | Método | Retorno |
|----------|--------|---------|
| 0 ou 1 registro | `.maybeSingle()` | objeto ou null |
| Exatamente 1 registro | `.single()` | objeto ou PGRST116 (not found) |
| Lista | (nenhum) | array |

```typescript
// Um registro opcional
const { data, error } = await supabase.from('patients').select('*').eq('id', id).maybeSingle();

// Um registro obrigatório (404 se não existir)
const { data, error } = await supabase.from('patients').select('*').eq('id', id).single();

// Lista
const { data, error } = await supabase.from('patients').select('*').eq('user_phone', phone);
```

## Erros

Always check `error`; on failure, throw. Never ignore.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const { data, error } = await supabase.from('patients').select('*').eq('id', id).single();
if (error) throw new Error(`Patient not found: ${error.message}`);
return data;

// ❌ BAD
const { data } = await supabase...;  // error ignorado
return data;
```

## Evitar N+1

- Use `.select('*, relation(*)')` for related data.
- Use batch `.insert([...])` instead of loop with single inserts.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD – one query com join
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('cases')
  .select('*, patients(*)')
  .eq('user_phone', userPhone);

// ❌ BAD – N+1
const cases = await getCases(userPhone);
for (const c of cases) {
  const patient = await getPatient(c.patient_id);  // N queries
}
```

## Insert / Update

Use `.insert(...).select('...').single()` (or `.maybeSingle()`) to return the created/updated row without an extra round-trip.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('patients')
  .insert({ user_phone, name, contact_phone })
  .select('id, name, created_at')
  .single();
if (error) throw new Error(`Failed to create patient: ${error.message}`);
return data;

// ❌ BAD – precisa de outra query para pegar o registro
await supabase.from('patients').insert({ ... });
const { data } = await supabase.from('patients').select('*').eq('id', ???).single();
```

## Performance

- Prefer indexed columns in filters (e.g. `user_phone`, `id`).
- Use `.order('created_at', { ascending: false })` for lists.
- Use `.limit()` or `.range()` for pagination.
